==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek [[ἥβη]] ‘youthful beauty’ (also [[Ἥβη]] ‘the goddess [[w:Hebe|Hebe]]’) + [[φρήν]] ‘mind’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/hi:bɪˈfri:nɪə/}}

===Noun===
'''hebephrenia'''
# ''(obsolete)'' A type of mental disorder occuring during puberty.
# A form of [[schizophrenia]] characterised by inappropriate behaviour and emotional responses.